hypotheses.hypothesis: Files that contain a high number of special characters and lack coherent text structure might contain bad data.
Files that contain a significantly higher average word count compared to the rest of the dataset might contain bad data.
Files that contain a significantly higher number of line breaks compared to the average number of line breaks in the dataset might contain bad data.
Files that contain content with a high frequency of repeated words or phrases might contain bad data.
Files that contain a significantly higher ratio of special characters to alphabetic characters in the content might contain bad data.
Files that contain content with an abnormally high frequency of single-letter words might contain bad data.
Files that contain a significantly higher number of punctuation marks compared to the average number of punctuation marks in the dataset might contain bad data.
Files that contain content with an unusually high frequency of non-alphabetic characters compared to the average frequency in the dataset might contain bad data.
Files that contain content with an uneven number of lines might contain bad data.
Files that contain content with an abnormally high frequency of repeated words might contain bad data.
